name: apache-spark-best-practices.mdc
description: Best practices for Apache Spark data processing
globs: **/*.py
---

- Use DataFrames for optimized performance and ease of use over RDDs.
- Leverage Spark's built-in functions for data transformations instead of UDFs when possible.
- Partition data effectively to improve parallel processing and reduce shuffling.
- Cache intermediate results when reusing data across multiple operations.
- Monitor Spark jobs using the Spark UI to identify bottlenecks and optimize resource allocation.
